x4freetext: The samples  of enriched up to more then 90% isotopes
(with the exception of Br and in) were used.
method of    cross   section   unfolding   from   the
Cross sections  of  gamma inelastic   scattering  with
excitation of isomer states of Se-77,  Br-79,  Sr-87,
Cd-111,  In-115, and Ba-137 nuclei were measured at 4
- 15 MeV energies in delta(E) = 0.5  MeV  steps.  For
the energy dependence of the isomer ratios
theta = sig-m/sig-tot was considered.  For nuclei
whose spins of the ground and  isomer  states  differ
by  delta(j)  =  4,  the dependence  theta  =  f(A)
was studied in a wide mass interval A = 77 - 197.
Increase of theta = f(A) with increase  of  A  is in
qualitative agreement with the statistical model
Data  were  prepared  in the MSU INP CDFE
